[
  {
    "text": "We live in a three-dimensional world",
    "start": 11.702,
    "duration": 2.025
  },
  {
    "text": "where everything has length,",
    "start": 13.751,
    "duration": 0.967
  },
  {
    "text": "width,",
    "start": 14.742,
    "duration": 0.603
  },
  {
    "text": "and height.",
    "start": 15.369,
    "duration": 1.386
  },
  {
    "text": "But what if our world\nwere two-dimensional?",
    "start": 16.779,
    "duration": 2.373
  },
  {
    "text": "We would be squashed down",
    "start": 19.176,
    "duration": 1.422
  },
  {
    "text": "to occupy a single plane of existence,",
    "start": 20.622,
    "duration": 2.488
  },
  {
    "text": "geometrically speaking, of course.",
    "start": 23.134,
    "duration": 1.99
  },
  {
    "text": "And what would that world\nlook and feel like?",
    "start": 25.148,
    "duration": 2.705
  },
  {
    "text": "This is the premise",
    "start": 27.877,
    "duration": 0.635
  },
  {
    "text": "of Edwin Abbott's 1884 novella, Flatland.",
    "start": 28.536,
    "duration": 3.495
  },
  {
    "text": "Flatland is a fun, mathematical\nthought experiment",
    "start": 32.055,
    "duration": 2.381
  },
  {
    "text": "that follows the trials\nand tribulations of a square",
    "start": 34.46,
    "duration": 2.578
  },
  {
    "text": "exposed to the third dimension.",
    "start": 37.062,
    "duration": 2.517
  },
  {
    "text": "But what is a dimension, anyway?",
    "start": 39.603,
    "duration": 2.356
  },
  {
    "text": "For our purposes,\na dimension is a direction,",
    "start": 41.983,
    "duration": 2.858
  },
  {
    "text": "which we can picture as a line.",
    "start": 44.865,
    "duration": 2.238
  },
  {
    "text": "For our direction to be a dimension,",
    "start": 47.127,
    "duration": 2.172
  },
  {
    "text": "it has to be at right angles\nto all other dimensions.",
    "start": 49.323,
    "duration": 4.01
  },
  {
    "text": "So, a one-dimensional\nspace is just a line.",
    "start": 53.357,
    "duration": 2.764
  },
  {
    "text": "A two-dimensional space is defined",
    "start": 56.145,
    "duration": 1.781
  },
  {
    "text": "by two perpendicular lines,",
    "start": 57.95,
    "duration": 2.131
  },
  {
    "text": "which describe a flat plane",
    "start": 60.105,
    "duration": 1.546
  },
  {
    "text": "like a piece of paper.",
    "start": 61.675,
    "duration": 1.612
  },
  {
    "text": "And a three-dimensional space",
    "start": 63.311,
    "duration": 1.381
  },
  {
    "text": "adds a third perpendicular line,",
    "start": 64.716,
    "duration": 2.022
  },
  {
    "text": "which gives us height",
    "start": 66.762,
    "duration": 1.258
  },
  {
    "text": "and the world we're familiar with.",
    "start": 68.044,
    "duration": 2.604
  },
  {
    "text": "So, what about four dimensions?",
    "start": 70.672,
    "duration": 1.8
  },
  {
    "text": "And five?",
    "start": 72.496,
    "duration": 0.958
  },
  {
    "text": "And eleven?",
    "start": 73.478,
    "duration": 1.093
  },
  {
    "text": "Where do we put these new\nperpendicular lines?",
    "start": 74.595,
    "duration": 2.686
  },
  {
    "text": "This is where Flatland can help us.",
    "start": 77.305,
    "duration": 2.511
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's look at our square\nprotagonist's world.",
    "start": 79.84,
    "duration": 2.873
  },
  {
    "text": "Flatland is populated by geometric shapes,",
    "start": 82.737,
    "duration": 2.504
  },
  {
    "text": "ranging from isosceles trianges",
    "start": 85.265,
    "duration": 1.644
  },
  {
    "text": "to equilateral triangles",
    "start": 86.933,
    "duration": 1.243
  },
  {
    "text": "to squares,",
    "start": 88.2,
    "duration": 0.765
  },
  {
    "text": "pentagons,",
    "start": 88.989,
    "duration": 0.505
  },
  {
    "text": "hexagons,",
    "start": 89.518,
    "duration": 0.571
  },
  {
    "text": "all the way up to circles.",
    "start": 90.113,
    "duration": 2.131
  },
  {
    "text": "These shapes are all scurrying\naround a flat world,",
    "start": 92.268,
    "duration": 2.739
  },
  {
    "text": "living their flat lives.",
    "start": 95.031,
    "duration": 1.727
  },
  {
    "text": "They have a single eye\non the front of their faces,",
    "start": 96.782,
    "duration": 2.651
  },
  {
    "text": "and let's see what the world looks like",
    "start": 99.457,
    "duration": 1.059
  },
  {
    "text": "from their perspective.",
    "start": 100.54,
    "duration": 1.892
  },
  {
    "text": "What they see is essentially\none dimension,",
    "start": 102.456,
    "duration": 2.868
  },
  {
    "text": "a line.",
    "start": 105.348,
    "duration": 1.087
  },
  {
    "text": "But in Abbott's Flatland,",
    "start": 106.459,
    "duration": 1.363
  },
  {
    "text": "closer objects are brighter,",
    "start": 107.846,
    "duration": 1.926
  },
  {
    "text": "and that's how they see depth.",
    "start": 109.796,
    "duration": 2.157
  },
  {
    "text": "So a triangle looks\ndifferent from a square,",
    "start": 111.977,
    "duration": 2.308
  },
  {
    "text": "looks different a circle,",
    "start": 114.309,
    "duration": 1.266
  },
  {
    "text": "and so on.",
    "start": 115.599,
    "duration": 1.275
  },
  {
    "text": "Their brains cannot comprehend\nthe third dimension.",
    "start": 116.898,
    "duration": 2.589
  },
  {
    "text": "In fact, they vehemently\ndeny its existence",
    "start": 119.511,
    "duration": 2.852
  },
  {
    "text": "because it's simply not\npart of their world",
    "start": 122.387,
    "duration": 2.147
  },
  {
    "text": "or experience.",
    "start": 124.558,
    "duration": 1.675
  },
  {
    "text": "But all they need,",
    "start": 126.257,
    "duration": 1.041
  },
  {
    "text": "as it turns out,",
    "start": 127.322,
    "duration": 1.138
  },
  {
    "text": "is a little boost.",
    "start": 128.484,
    "duration": 2.09
  },
  {
    "text": "One day a sphere shows up in Flatland",
    "start": 130.598,
    "duration": 1.894
  },
  {
    "text": "to visit our square hero.",
    "start": 132.516,
    "duration": 1.725
  },
  {
    "text": "Here's what it looks like",
    "start": 134.265,
    "duration": 0.913
  },
  {
    "text": "when the sphere passes through Flatland",
    "start": 135.202,
    "duration": 2.123
  },
  {
    "text": "from the square's perspective,",
    "start": 137.349,
    "duration": 2.492
  },
  {
    "text": "and this blows his little square mind.",
    "start": 139.865,
    "duration": 2.6
  },
  {
    "text": "Then the sphere lifts the square",
    "start": 142.489,
    "duration": 1.862
  },
  {
    "text": "into the third dimension,",
    "start": 144.375,
    "duration": 1.514
  },
  {
    "text": "the height direction where no\nFlatlander has gone before",
    "start": 145.913,
    "duration": 3.025
  },
  {
    "text": "and shows him his world.",
    "start": 148.962,
    "duration": 1.981
  },
  {
    "text": "From up here, the square\ncan see everything:",
    "start": 150.967,
    "duration": 2.561
  },
  {
    "text": "the shapes of buildings,",
    "start": 153.552,
    "duration": 1.056
  },
  {
    "text": "all the precious gems hidden in the Earth,",
    "start": 154.632,
    "duration": 2.117
  },
  {
    "text": "and even the insides of his friends,",
    "start": 156.773,
    "duration": 2.548
  },
  {
    "text": "which is probably pretty awkward.",
    "start": 159.345,
    "duration": 2.648
  },
  {
    "text": "Once the hapless square",
    "start": 162.017,
    "duration": 1.098
  },
  {
    "text": "comes to terms with the third dimension,",
    "start": 163.139,
    "duration": 1.729
  },
  {
    "text": "he begs his host to help him",
    "start": 164.892,
    "duration": 1.364
  },
  {
    "text": "visit the fourth and higher dimensions,",
    "start": 166.28,
    "duration": 2.217
  },
  {
    "text": "but the sphere bristles\nat the mere suggestion",
    "start": 168.521,
    "duration": 2.191
  },
  {
    "text": "of dimensions higher than three",
    "start": 170.736,
    "duration": 1.594
  },
  {
    "text": "and exiles the square back to Flatland.",
    "start": 172.354,
    "duration": 2.974
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, the sphere's indignation\nis understandable.",
    "start": 175.352,
    "duration": 2.475
  },
  {
    "text": "A fourth dimension is very difficult",
    "start": 177.851,
    "duration": 1.715
  },
  {
    "text": "to reconcile with our experience\nof the world.",
    "start": 179.59,
    "duration": 2.595
  },
  {
    "text": "Short of being lifted\ninto the fourth dimension",
    "start": 182.209,
    "duration": 2.239
  },
  {
    "text": "by visiting hypercube,",
    "start": 184.472,
    "duration": 1.086
  },
  {
    "text": "we can't experience it,",
    "start": 185.582,
    "duration": 1.909
  },
  {
    "text": "but we can get close.",
    "start": 187.515,
    "duration": 1.631
  },
  {
    "text": "You'll recall that when the sphere",
    "start": 189.17,
    "duration": 1.351
  },
  {
    "text": "first visited the second dimension,",
    "start": 190.545,
    "duration": 1.895
  },
  {
    "text": "he looked like a series of circles",
    "start": 192.464,
    "duration": 1.775
  },
  {
    "text": "that started as a point",
    "start": 194.263,
    "duration": 1.176
  },
  {
    "text": "when he touched Flatland,",
    "start": 195.463,
    "duration": 1.394
  },
  {
    "text": "grew bigger until he was halfway through,",
    "start": 196.881,
    "duration": 2.284
  },
  {
    "text": "and then shrank smaller again.",
    "start": 199.189,
    "duration": 1.973
  },
  {
    "text": "We can think of this visit",
    "start": 201.186,
    "duration": 1.306
  },
  {
    "text": "as a series of 2D\ncross-sections of a 3D object.",
    "start": 202.516,
    "duration": 4.142
  },
  {
    "text": "Well, we can do the same thing",
    "start": 206.682,
    "duration": 1.429
  },
  {
    "text": "in the third dimension\nwith a four-dimensional object.",
    "start": 208.135,
    "duration": 4.061
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's say that a hypersphere",
    "start": 212.22,
    "duration": 1.334
  },
  {
    "text": "is the 4D equivalent of a 3D sphere.",
    "start": 213.578,
    "duration": 2.812
  },
  {
    "text": "When the 4D object passes\nthrough the third dimension,",
    "start": 216.414,
    "duration": 2.887
  },
  {
    "text": "it'll look something like this.",
    "start": 219.325,
    "duration": 2.583
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's look at one more way",
    "start": 221.932,
    "duration": 1.076
  },
  {
    "text": "of representing a four-dimensional object.",
    "start": 223.032,
    "duration": 2.676
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's say we have a point,",
    "start": 225.732,
    "duration": 0.86
  },
  {
    "text": "a zero-dimensional shape.",
    "start": 226.616,
    "duration": 2.054
  },
  {
    "text": "Now we extend it out one inch",
    "start": 228.694,
    "duration": 1.518
  },
  {
    "text": "and we have a one-dimensional\nline segment.",
    "start": 230.236,
    "duration": 2.562
  },
  {
    "text": "Extend the whole line segment by an inch,",
    "start": 232.822,
    "duration": 2.066
  },
  {
    "text": "and we get a 2D square.",
    "start": 234.912,
    "duration": 2.134
  },
  {
    "text": "Take the whole square\nand extend it out one inch,",
    "start": 237.07,
    "duration": 2.334
  },
  {
    "text": "and we get a 3D cube.",
    "start": 239.428,
    "duration": 1.913
  },
  {
    "text": "You can see where we're going with this.",
    "start": 241.365,
    "duration": 1.626
  },
  {
    "text": "Take the whole cube",
    "start": 243.015,
    "duration": 1.138
  },
  {
    "text": "and extend it out one inch,",
    "start": 244.177,
    "duration": 1.332
  },
  {
    "text": "this time perpendicular\nto all three existing directions,",
    "start": 245.533,
    "duration": 3.308
  },
  {
    "text": "and we get a 4D hypercube,",
    "start": 248.865,
    "duration": 2.369
  },
  {
    "text": "also called a tesseract.",
    "start": 251.258,
    "duration": 2.544
  },
  {
    "text": "For all we know,",
    "start": 253.826,
    "duration": 0.939
  },
  {
    "text": "there could be four-dimensional lifeforms",
    "start": 254.789,
    "duration": 1.552
  },
  {
    "text": "somewhere out there,",
    "start": 256.365,
    "duration": 1.229
  },
  {
    "text": "occasionally poking their heads",
    "start": 257.618,
    "duration": 1.477
  },
  {
    "text": "into our bustling 3D world",
    "start": 259.119,
    "duration": 1.815
  },
  {
    "text": "and wondering what all the fuss is about.",
    "start": 260.958,
    "duration": 2.163
  },
  {
    "text": "In fact, there could be whole",
    "start": 263.145,
    "duration": 1.142
  },
  {
    "text": "other four-dimensional worlds",
    "start": 264.311,
    "duration": 1.746
  },
  {
    "text": "beyond our detection,",
    "start": 266.081,
    "duration": 1.461
  },
  {
    "text": "hidden from us forever",
    "start": 267.566,
    "duration": 0.979
  },
  {
    "text": "by the nature of our perception.",
    "start": 268.569,
    "duration": 2.358
  },
  {
    "text": "Doesn't that blow\nyour little spherical mind?",
    "start": 270.951,
    "duration": 3.252
  }
]